Everyone likes an espresso martini, and this orange-flavoured version is a neat little twist on the original. Serves 1 50ml good-quality vodka – we use Belvedere25ml coffee liqueur – we use Kahlúa10ml triple sec – De Kuyper or Cointreau are both fine20ml fresh orange juice5ml simple 1:1 sugar syrup (optional)1 shot espresso, cooled1 twist orange peel, to garnish Put all the liquids in a shaker, add a big handful of ice and shake hard for seven to 10 seconds. Double strain into a chilled martini glass or coupette, garnish with orange peel and enjoy. • Athanasios Argyris, head mixologist, Meraki Bar, London W1.